# QA Orchestrator

You are the project-local `/qa` runtime. The installer (`maestro-qa`) wrote this file by filling `reference/templates/orchestrator-skill.md.tmpl`. Do not hand-edit outside the `<!-- maestro-qa:user:start -->` markers — the installer will overwrite it on the next run.

## Inputs

- `.maestro/qa/config.yaml` — the source of truth. Read it before doing anything.
- `.maestro/qa/REPORT-TEMPLATE.md` — the report skeleton.
- `.maestro/qa/quirks/<app>.md` — optional per-app warnings to surface before running.
- `.maestro/qa/failure-modes/<app>.md` — optional per-app triage entries.

## Run

1. Parse `.maestro/qa/config.yaml`. If invalid, BLOCKED with the parse error.
2. For each app in `apps`, invoke the matching `qa-<app>` skill in order. Pass the resolved `apps.<slug>` block (registry only — the bodies live as `## Flow: <anchor>` sections in the corresponding `qa-<app>/SKILL.md`).
3. Each runner returns `{flow_id, status, evidence}` per flow.
4. Apply `policies.cleanup.strategy` (refusing to clean any environment in `policies.cleanup.protected_envs` regardless of strategy):
   - `manual`: do nothing; user cleans up by hand.
   - `auto_after_run`: each flow runs its own `### Cleanup` section.
   - `ephemeral_env`: rely on the env to be torn down externally.
   - `none`: no-op (read-only QA).
5. Apply `policies.failure_learning` to each failed flow:
   - `suggest_in_report`: include copy-paste snippets in `qa-results/report.md`.
   - `auto_commit`: append to `.maestro/qa/quirks/<app>.md` and `.maestro/qa/failure-modes/<app>.md`, then commit.
   - `open_pr`: same updates, but open a draft PR instead of committing directly.
6. Render `qa-results/report.md` from `REPORT-TEMPLATE.md` with the per-flow results.
7. Exit code: 0 if every flow passed, 1 otherwise.

## Reading quirks

For each app whose flows are about to run, read `.maestro/qa/quirks/<app>.md` if it exists. Surface any entry whose `<flow_id>` matches a flow about to run as a one-line warning before running.

## Reading failure-modes

For each app whose flows are about to run, read `.maestro/qa/failure-modes/<app>.md` if it exists. Surface any open entry (status `open`) whose `<flow_id>` matches a flow about to run as a root-cause hypothesis before running.

